[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mASAN[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected a segmentation fault [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the curl library[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring fuzzing operations. The crash occurs in the `Curl_doh_close` function at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m of `[0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m`, triggered by a READ memory access to an invalid[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhigh-value address. This represents a wild pointer dereference vulnerability with a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSCARINESS score of [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Overview[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer `curl_fuzzer_http` encountered a critical memory access violation when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing a test case. The crash is classified as a SEGV [0m[1;39m([0m[39msegmentation fault[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcaused by attempting to read from an invalid memory address. The AddressSanitizer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mframework identified this as a [0m[32m"wild-addr-read,"[0m[39m indicating that the code is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereferencing a pointer with an unusually high or invalid address value.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a memory safety issue, specifically:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Segmentation Fault [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Invalid memory access violation[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Wild Pointer Dereference**: The fault was caused by dereferencing a pointer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontaining an invalid high-value address[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **READ Access Violation**: The crash occurred during a read operation[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Stack Trace Analysis[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash occurs through the following call chain:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Point**: `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in the fuzzer harness [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/src/curl_fuzzer/[0m[95mcurl_fuzzer.cc[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m97[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Transfer Handling**: `fuzz_handle_transfer` [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/src/curl_fuzzer/[0m[95mcurl_fuzzer.cc[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m419[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Multi Interface**: `curl_multi_perform` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mmulti.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m3016[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Request Processing**: `multi_runsingle` → `multi_done` → `Curl_req_done`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Crash Location**: `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash point at line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m in `doh.c` suggests that the function is attempting to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess a field or dereference a pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mindicated by [0m[32m"`:30`"[0m[39m column offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontains an invalid address.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Important Observations[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **DoH [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDNS over HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Component**: The crash occurs in the DoH close function, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the issue is related to DNS over HTTPS functionality cleanup or resource[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeallocation.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Request Cleanup Path**: The failure happens during request cleanup [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m after a multi operation, suggesting improper state management or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muninitialized/corrupted pointers during the teardown phase.[0m                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:113[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m127[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req, struct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:  struct curltime t0 = [0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* This is a bit ugly. `req->p` is a union and we assume we can[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:   * free this safely without leaks. *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m119[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->p.ftp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m120[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->newurl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m121[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m122[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->sendbuf_init[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_bufq_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&req->sendbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m124[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis Summary[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and the crash report, I have identified the root [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause of the segmentation fault:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash occurs due to a **dangling pointer issue** in `data->req.doh`. The [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifecycle management of the DoH structure is incomplete in certain code paths:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh.[0m[1;92mc:1402[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1429[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only closes probe handles but does NOT [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfree or nullify `data->req.doh`[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1440[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m properly closes, frees, AND nullifies[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrequest.[0m[1;92mc:108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and **`[0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mrequest.[0m[1;92mc:126[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m call `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but do NOT nullify `data->req.doh` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafterwards[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. When DoH resolution completes in **`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_is_resolved[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh.[0m[1;92mc:1316[0m[39m, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1393[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it calls both `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, freeing and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnullifying the pointer[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. However, if the request lifecycle continues and `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlater [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas shown in the crash trace: multi_done → Curl_req_done → Curl_doh_close[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit attempts to access the already-freed memory[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Critical Code Flow Leading to Crash[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDoH resolution completes:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_is_resolved[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    → [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m          [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcloses handles, doh pointer still valid[0m[1;39m][0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    → [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m        [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mfrees memory, sets data->req.doh = NULL[0m[1;39m][0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRequest completion later:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mmulti_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    → [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      → [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m        [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mCRASH: doh pointer should be NULL but might be[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdangling[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        → line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m: mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;  [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mwild pointer dereference[0m[1;39m][0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, there's a subtlety: if `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` properly nullified the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer, why does the crash still occur? The issue is likely that:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Request reuse scenarios where `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_soft_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare called[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- These functions call `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but don't nullify `data->req.doh`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If the DoH structure was freed elsewhere, the pointer becomes dangling[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The check `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m1405[0m[39m doesn't catch this because a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed pointer is non-NULL[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Nullify DoH Pointer After Closing[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: lib/request.c - `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` function**[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter line [0m[1;36m108[0m[39m where `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called, add:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  data->req.doh = NULL;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add this line[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#endif[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: lib/request.c - `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` function**[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter line [0m[1;36m126[0m[39m where `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called, add:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  data->req.doh = NULL;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add this line  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#endif[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Secondary Fix: Defensive Check in Curl_doh_close[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhile the primary fix addresses the root cause, add an additional safety check in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to validate the pointer before dereferencing:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: lib/doh.c - `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` function**[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify the condition at line [0m[1;36m1405[0m[39m to be more defensive. However, checking for a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdangling pointer is not possible directly. Instead, the fix should rely on proper [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnullification in the calling code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprimary fix above[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAlternatively, if we want to make `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` responsible for nullification,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodify it to:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvoid [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m existing code to close probe handles [0m[33m...[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Do NOT nullify here as Curl_doh_close is meant to only close handles,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m not free the structure. Callers must nullify if they don't free immediately.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe design intent is clear: `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` closes handles, `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcloses and frees. The bug is that intermediate callers don't properly manage the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer state.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Fix is Optimal[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Architecture**: The separation between `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mclose handles[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfree memory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is intentional. We maintain [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis design while fixing the lifecycle issue.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Impact**: Only adding nullification in two locations where [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called without subsequent memory freeing.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Consistent with Codebase Patterns**: The fix follows the same pattern used by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` macro which nullifies after freeing.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Addresses All Code Paths**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` called during normal request completion[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` called during request reuse/reset[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both now properly nullify the pointer after closing[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Prevents Future Issues**: Even if `data->req.doh` is freed elsewhere [0m[1;39m([0m[39mby [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, subsequent calls to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will safely skip the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereference due to NULL check at line [0m[1;36m1405[0m[39m.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m**: If code expects `data->req.doh` to remain valid after [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, this could break that assumption.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: Analysis of the codebase shows:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_is_resolved[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls both `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min sequence [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1316[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m1393[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so nullification won't affect it[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No other code accesses `data->req.doh` after `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in the request lifecycle[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The DEBUGASSERT at doh.[0m[1;92mc:423[0m[39m expects `data->req.doh` to be NULL before [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation, confirming this is the intended state[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m**: Memory leak if `data->req.doh` points to allocated memory that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhasn't been freed.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The only allocation is in doh.[0m[1;92mc:427[0m[39m via `[0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The only freeing is in `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` via `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Request lifecycle ensures `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_free[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring final cleanup[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Setting to NULL after `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in intermediate stages doesn't cause [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleaks because:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Either the structure was already freed by `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnullification [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents double-free[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Or the structure will be freed later by `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_free[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Alternative Approaches Considered and Rejected[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Alternative [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m**: Replace `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in both [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocations.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rejected because**: This would free the memory earlier than intended, potentially[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbreaking code that expects the DoH structure to remain valid for longer. The design[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseparates closing handles from freeing memory for a reason.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Alternative [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m**: Modify `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to free and nullify the pointer.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rejected because**: This would change the semantics of `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially break other callers that expect it to only close handles. The function [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mname suggests [0m[32m"close"[0m[39m not [0m[32m"cleanup/free"[0m[39m.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Alternative [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m**: Add memory validation checks in `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rejected because**: There's no reliable way to detect if a pointer is dangling [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvs. valid in C. The proper solution is lifecycle management, not runtime detection.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix strategy is optimal because:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses the Root Cause**: Prevents dangling pointer by nullifying after [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosing handles[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Code Changes**: Only [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m lines added in [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m locations[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Maintains Design Intent**: Preserves separation between close and cleanup [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Consistent with Codebase**: Follows existing patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `Curl_safefree` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmacro[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Breaking Changes**: Doesn't affect external APIs or test behavior[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Prevents Similar Issues**: Makes the code more robust against future lifecycle[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbugs[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix ensures that `data->req.doh` is either:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- NULL [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafe to check in `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m1405[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid pointer to allocated memory [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafe to dereference at line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Never a dangling pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich was causing the crash[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Request cleanup flow**: The sequence `Curl_req_done` → `multi_done` → [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What sequence of operations it triggers[0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m857[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Remove the association between the connection and the handle *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m858[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_detach_connection[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m859[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m860[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->set.connect_only && !data->multi_easy[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m861[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* This removes a handle that was part the multi interface that used[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m862[0m[39m:       CONNECT_ONLY, that connection is now left alive but since this handle[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m863[0m[39m:       has bits.close set nothing can use that transfer anymore and it is[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m864[0m[39m:       forbidden from reuse. This easy handle cannot find the connection[0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m867[0m[39m:       Better close the connection here, at once.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m868[0m[39m:    *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m869[0m[39m:    struct connectdata *c;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m872[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms != CURL_SOCKET_BAD[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:  struct curltime t0 = [0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* This is a bit ugly. `req->p` is a union and we assume we can[0m               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:170[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m183[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_req_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req, struct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* This is a bit ugly. `req->p` is a union and we assume we can[0m               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->sendbuf_init[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
