[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:  data = [0m[1;35mCurl_multi_get_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->multi, doh->set.dohfor_mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mDEBUGF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh, [0m[32m"doh_done: xfer for [0m[32mmid[0m[32m=%"[0m[39m FMT_OFF_T[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:                 [0m[32m" not found"[0m[39m, doh->set.dohfor_mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:  else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:    struct doh_probes *dohp = data->req.doh;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* one of the DoH request done for the [0m[32m'data'[0m[39m transfer is now complete! *[0m[35m/[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:    dohp->pending--;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh, [0m[32m"a DoH request is completed, %u to go"[0m[39m, dohp->pending[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh, [0m[32m"DoH request %s"[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mcurl_easy_strerror[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!dohp->pending[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* DoH completed, run the transfer picking up the results *[0m[35m/[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mCurl_expire[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, EXPIRE_RUN_NOW[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m237[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m238[0m[39m:  return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.h:[0m[1;36m61[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m97[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m* one of these for each DoH request *[0m[35m/[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:struct doh_probe [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:  curl_off_t easy_mid; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* multi id of easy handle doing the lookup *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:  DNStype dnstype;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:  unsigned char req_body[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m512[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:  size_t req_body_len;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:  struct dynbuf resp_body;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m70:e[0m[39mnum doh_slot_num [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Explicit values for first two symbols so as to match hard-coded[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:   * constants in existing code[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:   *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:  DOH_SLOT_IPV4 = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[35m/[0m[39m* make [0m[32m'V4'[0m[39m stand out for readability *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m:  DOH_SLOT_IPV6 = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[32m'V6'[0m[39m likewise *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Space here for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpossibly build-specific[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m additional slot definitions *[0m[35m/[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:#ifdef USE_HTTPSRR[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:  DOH_SLOT_HTTPS_RR = [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m,     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* for HTTPS RR *[0m[35m/[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* for example *[0m[35m/[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* #ifdef WANT_DOH_FOOBAR_TXT *[0m[35m/[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m*   DOH_PROBE_SLOT_FOOBAR_TXT, *[0m[35m/[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* #endif *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* AFTER all slot definitions, establish how many we have *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:  DOH_SLOT_COUNT[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:struct doh_probes [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:  struct curl_slist *req_hds;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:  struct doh_probe probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_COUNT[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:  unsigned int pending; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* still outstanding probes *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:  int port;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:  const char *host;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis Summary[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and evaluation reports, I've identified the root [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause of the crash:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash occurs due to a lifecycle management issue between parent DOH handles and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtheir probe handles:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. When `[0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called on a parent handle with active DOH probes, it [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls `[0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m245[0m[39m in url.c[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Inside `curl_multi_remove_handle`, at line [0m[1;36m822[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m829[0m[39m in multi.c, `[0m[1;35mmulti_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly called if `data->conn` exists[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. For DOH resolution scenarios, `data->conn` can be NULL [0m[1;39m([0m[39mresolution happens [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore connection establishment[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. When `data->conn` is NULL, `[0m[1;35mmulti_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is skipped, which means [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is never called[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. After the removal logic completes, `data->multi` is set to NULL at line [0m[1;36m901[0m[39m in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti.c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Later at line [0m[1;36m265[0m[39m in url.c, `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_free[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtries to call `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. However, `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` has a guard condition `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m1405[0m[39m in doh.c, which fails because `data->multi` is now NULL[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. The probe handles are never removed from the multi handle and never closed[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m9[0m[39m. When these orphaned probes complete, their `doh_done` callback tries to access [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe parent's `data->req.doh`, which has been freed, causing a SEGV crash[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch attempted to fix this by:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Storing `data->multi` in a local variable[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Setting `data->req.doh = NULL` early[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using the local `multi` variable[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, this doesn't address the fundamental issue: the guard condition still [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents cleanup when `data->multi` is NULL, and the probe handles are still left [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the multi handle.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Fix Strategy[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must ensure that DOH probe cleanup happens before `data->multi` is cleared,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregardless of whether `data->conn` exists. Here's the comprehensive strategy:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Add Direct DOH Cleanup Call in `curl_multi_remove_handle`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<file>lib/multi.[0m[1;92mc:822[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m901[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfile[0m[39m>[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `curl_multi_remove_handle` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add a call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclearing `data->multi`:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** After line [0m[1;36m829[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter the `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->conn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and before line [0m[1;36m901[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`data->multi = NULL`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation:**[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add `#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH` guard[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` unconditionally before setting `data->multi = NULL`[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This ensures probes are cleaned up even when `data->conn` is NULL[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Place it after all other cleanup operations but before `data->multi = NULL` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m888[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m900[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Reasoning:** This guarantees that DOH probes are removed and closed while [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->multi` is still valid, regardless of whether `[0m[1;35mmulti_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was called. This[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandles the case where `data->conn` is NULL during DOH resolution.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Make `Curl_doh_close` More Resilient[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** lib/doh.c, lines [0m[1;36m1402[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1429[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation:**[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Remove the `data->multi` check from the guard condition at line [0m[1;36m1405[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to just `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Store `data->multi` in a local variable at the beginning[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use the local variable for all operations[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add NULL checks before using the local multi variable for each operation[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- For probe removal, skip `curl_multi_remove_handle` if multi is NULL, but still [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall `[0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to ensure probe handles are freed[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Reasoning:** This makes the function handle both scenarios:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When called with valid `data->multi`: Normal cleanup through multi handle[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When called with NULL `data->multi`: Direct cleanup of probe handles without [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti removal[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Add NULL Check in `doh_done` Callback[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** lib/doh.c, lines [0m[1;36m214[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m238[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation:**[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After line [0m[1;36m226[0m[39m where `dohp = data->req.doh` is assigned[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a NULL check: `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!dohp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This prevents crashes if the parent's DOH structure has been freed[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Reasoning:** This provides defense-in-depth. Even if probe cleanup ordering [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missues occur, the callback won't crash when accessing freed memory.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Prevent Double Cleanup Issues[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** lib/doh.c, line [0m[1;36m1435[0m[39m in `Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation:**[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Set `data->req.doh = NULL` immediately after calling `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This prevents use-after-free if `Curl_doh_cleanup` is called multiple times[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use a local pointer to access the doh structure after setting it to NULL[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Reasoning:** Multiple cleanup paths exist [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom `Curl_req_done`, [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_hard_reset`, `Curl_req_free`, and `Curl_doh_is_resolved`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Setting it to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL early prevents double-free or use-after-free issues.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Summary of Changes[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix involves modifications to two files:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**lib/multi.c:**[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call before setting `data->multi = NULL` in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`curl_multi_remove_handle`[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**lib/doh.c:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modify `Curl_doh_close` to work with NULL `data->multi` by using local variable [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand adding NULL checks[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add NULL check for `dohp` in `doh_done` callback[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Set `data->req.doh = NULL` early in `Curl_doh_cleanup` to prevent double cleanup[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Approach is Optimal[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses Root Cause:** Ensures DOH probes are cleaned up before `data->multi`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis cleared[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Handles All Scenarios:** Works whether `data->conn` is NULL or not[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth:** Multiple safety checks prevent crashes even if ordering [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missues occur[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic:** Doesn't break existing cleanup paths[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Breaking Changes:** Maintains the same API and behavior for all other use [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Minimal Invasiveness:** Changes are localized to DOH-specific code paths[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Double Cleanup:** Setting `data->req.doh = NULL` early prevents this[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Probe Handles Left in Multi:** Direct `[0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call ensures they're [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed even if multi removal fails[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Callback Reentrancy:** NULL checks in `doh_done` prevent crashes during [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconcurrent cleanup[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
